OL,7,FThey added: "This change supports
OL,8,Fvictims and society alike. It shows
OL,9,Fjustice being done.
OL,11,F"It gives families a moment of
OL,12,Frecognition and a form of reparation.
OL,13,FIt is a moment of reckoning for the
OL,14,Fconvicted."
OL,16,FPrime Minister Sir Keir Starmer
OL,17,Fpromised to carry on the pledge to
OL,18,Fchange the law, first made by his
OL,19,Fpredecessor Rishi Sunak, when he met
OL,20,Fthe mother of murdered nine-year-old
OL,21,FOlivia Pratt-Korbel.
